Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13),
               cmake,
               pkg-config,
               libasound2-dev,
               libavahi-client-dev
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: mp3-player
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: avahi-daemon
Description: TCP-controlled MP3 player
 Send base64-encoded MP3 bytes over a plain TCP connection and it plays
 immediately over ALSA. There is no filename or library concept, and
 nothing is ever written to disk. Only one track plays at a time; while
 busy, new connections get an error instead of interrupting playback.
 Decoding uses a vendored public-domain MP3 decoder (no external decode
 library). Announces itself on the LAN as _mp3player._tcp via mDNS/DNS-SD
 when avahi-daemon is available.
 .
 There is no web UI — the protocol is driven by nc or scripts.
 .
 Protocol     : TCP :<8566>  (base64 MP3 in, JSON status line out)
 Discovery    : mDNS/DNS-SD, service type _mp3player._tcp
 Config       : /etc/mp3-player/config.ini
